{"id":"recVvlL5y8Amm6t58","ref":"1Cor.3.2","text":"I have fed you with milk, and not with meat: for hitherto ye were not able to bear it, neither yet now are ye able.","year":59},{"id":"recJwkZTjlOV04aS9","ref":"1Cor.3.3","text":"For ye are yet carnal: for whereas there is among you envying, and strife, and divisions, are ye not carnal, and walk as men?","year":59},{"id":"recJ8SSxvl6RCsTFv","ref":"1Cor.3.4","text":"For while one saith, I am of Paul; and another, I am of Apollos; are ye not carnal?","year":59},{"id":"recvFsESmBmYk9Wms","ref":"1Cor.3.5","text":"Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom ye believed, even as the Lord gave to every man?","year":59},{"id":"recgmPjTYXqPT1Qsw","ref":"1Cor.3.6","text":"I have planted, Apollos watered; but God gave the increase.","year":59},{"id":"rec6WiFFgTIOWeG99","ref":"1Cor.3.7","text":"So then neither is he that planteth any thing, neither he that watereth; but God that giveth the increase.","year":59},{"id":"rec8NuKRXIc1gE7wF","ref":"1Cor.3.8","text":"Now he that planteth and he that watereth are one: and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labour.","year":59}]}
